SIMPLE: meanly
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Meanly
<hw>Mean"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[<er>Mean</er> middle.]</ety>
<def>Moderately.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A man <qex>meanly</qex> learned himself, but not <qex>meanly</qex>
affectioned to set forward learning in others.</q>
<rj><qau>Ascham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meanly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Meanly
<hw>Mean"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Mean</er> low.]</ety>
<def>In a mean manner; unworthily; basely; poorly;
ungenerously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>While the heaven-born child⟦br⟧
All <qex>meanly</qex> wrapt in the rude manger lies.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Would you <qex>meanly</qex> thus rely⟦br⟧
On power you know I must obey ?</q> <rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We can not bear to have others think <qex>meanly</qex> of them
[our kindred].</q> <rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meanness</ent>⟦br⟧
